00:03:22.050 --> 00:03:25.360
But now please join me in
welcoming Eric Gansworth,

00:03:25.360 --> 00:03:30.510
Linda LeGarde Grover, Stephen
Graham Jones, and Deborah Miranda.

00:03:30.510 --> 00:03:36.510
[ Applause ]

00:03:36.510 --> 00:03:43.940
[ Pause ]

00:03:43.940 --> 00:03:45.240
&gt;&gt; Eric Gansworth: Good afternoon.

00:03:45.240 --> 00:03:46.540
Thank you for coming.

00:03:46.540 --> 00:03:48.130
Thank you to The Library
of Congress for inviting me

00:03:48.130 --> 00:03:50.720
to participate in this event.

00:03:50.720 --> 00:03:53.630
It's really delightful to
be here on the same occasion

00:03:53.630 --> 00:03:55.710 position:56%
as Louse's new novel being launched,

00:03:55.710 --> 00:03:58.950
which I'm sure many people are very
excited about, as much as I am.

00:03:58.950 --> 00:04:00.670
I'm going to read an excerpt

00:04:00.670 --> 00:04:02.920
from a forthcoming
novel, Give Me Some Truth.

00:04:02.920 --> 00:04:06.330
It is a follow-up to my last
novel, If I Ever Get Out of Here.

00:04:06.330 --> 00:04:10.900
I'm working on a four-novel
sequence of Beatle's books.

00:04:10.900 --> 00:04:14.440
I'm not really sure what's going
to happen when we get to Ringo,

00:04:14.440 --> 00:04:21.230
but so this is the first chapter
from this narrative point of view,

00:04:21.230 --> 00:04:24.440
this is the John and Yoko book
so they get equal billing.

00:04:24.440 --> 00:04:29.040
And so this is from a 15-year-old
girl who is a bead worker.

00:04:31.480 --> 00:04:34.880
Are you from an Indian reservation
near here, the new groom asked,

00:04:34.880 --> 00:04:36.390
while his bride eyed up a pair

00:04:36.390 --> 00:04:39.530
of beadwork dangle
earrings from our display.

00:04:39.530 --> 00:04:42.000
Technically, my sister Marie said.

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:44.610
Immediately new groom's
ears perked up.

00:04:44.610 --> 00:04:47.900
He clearly didn't want to
be buying fake Indian goods.

00:04:47.900 --> 00:04:51.920
Either you are or you aren't
Indian, isn't that right, he asked.

00:04:51.920 --> 00:04:53.920
Our mom was walking back
from the lady's room,

00:04:53.920 --> 00:04:56.450
a half million miles
from our vendor's table.

00:04:56.450 --> 00:05:00.910
Marie never engaged in her mild
sabotage when our mom was around.

00:05:00.910 --> 00:05:02.340
It was Memorial Day weekend,

00:05:02.340 --> 00:05:05.720
the beginning of our season
selling handmade Indian souvenirs

00:05:05.720 --> 00:05:07.720
at Niagara Falls State Park.

00:05:07.720 --> 00:05:10.760
We personally enforced
our tribal treaties

00:05:10.760 --> 00:05:12.870
with the likes of New York State.

00:05:12.870 --> 00:05:14.170
It gives you a sense of power

00:05:14.170 --> 00:05:18.770
in your otherwise woefully
powerless 15-year-old girl life.

00:05:18.770 --> 00:05:22.350
Oh, yeah, we are definitely
Indian, Marie said,

00:05:22.350 --> 00:05:25.050
don't my beautiful
red skin prove it?

00:05:25.050 --> 00:05:29.020
New groom was edgy, but new bride
had already locked her tractor beam

00:05:29.020 --> 00:05:31.840
eyes on the earrings.

00:05:31.840 --> 00:05:33.140
We just don't live

00:05:33.140 --> 00:05:35.380
on the reservation
anymore, but I wish we did.

00:05:35.380 --> 00:05:36.680
Most of our family does,

00:05:36.680 --> 00:05:40.240
and I'm tired of living
in the city, Marie said.

00:05:40.240 --> 00:05:43.740
Suddenly switching
to her forlorn tone.

00:05:43.740 --> 00:05:45.970
Our mom greeted our
potential customers

00:05:45.970 --> 00:05:50.820
with the humble Indian craftsperson
face she had mastered years ago.

00:05:50.820 --> 00:05:54.730
We longed to be among our people,
I said, going along with Marie.

00:05:54.730 --> 00:05:57.750
Trying out new routines
could be fun.

00:05:57.750 --> 00:06:01.220
So why aren't you among your
people, new groom asked.

00:06:01.220 --> 00:06:03.620
A lot of tourists ask
this pushy question,

00:06:03.620 --> 00:06:06.900
testing to see if we
were real Indians.

00:06:06.900 --> 00:06:08.280
Our vendor permit was pinned

00:06:08.280 --> 00:06:10.250
to the appropriately ingenie
[Assumed Spelling] Pendleton

00:06:10.250 --> 00:06:11.780
covering our table.

00:06:11.780 --> 00:06:15.160
The Parks Department required
it be visible at all times,

00:06:15.160 --> 00:06:17.600
the permit, not the Pendleton.

00:06:18.830 --> 00:06:24.140
Sad fact, I said, adopting my own
version of forlorn Indian, Indians,

00:06:24.140 --> 00:06:26.270
they don't buy much beadwork.

00:06:26.270 --> 00:06:30.220
A little lie, they tended to buy
only a certain kind of beadwork.

00:06:30.220 --> 00:06:34.060
Keychains, trucker caps or baseball
caps, disposable lighter cases,

00:06:34.060 --> 00:06:37.110
bingo bags and eyeglass cases.

00:06:37.110 --> 00:06:43.750
So here we are building bridges to
the larger culture with our art.

00:06:43.750 --> 00:06:49.250
I modeled my look on the
crying antipollution TV Indian.

00:06:49.250 --> 00:06:53.590
This broach is designed by my
elders to go with the earrings.

00:06:53.590 --> 00:06:56.540
I slid a little basswood
carving forward.

00:06:56.540 --> 00:06:58.850
My dad made it last week.

00:06:58.850 --> 00:07:01.750
The expression on new bride's
face said she couldn't see herself

00:07:01.750 --> 00:07:03.050
in this combo.

00:07:03.050 --> 00:07:06.540
She didn't love Indians that much.

00:07:06.540 --> 00:07:10.590
This is our specialty, I added,
revealing one of our canoes,

00:07:10.590 --> 00:07:13.590
which I did whenever
I saw that expression.

00:07:13.590 --> 00:07:16.700
In my best mystical Indian
voice, all clipped confidence

00:07:16.700 --> 00:07:19.670
and draggy vowels,
the works, I said,

00:07:19.670 --> 00:07:24.400
each Indian family has
their own signature,

00:07:24.400 --> 00:07:30.860
ours is the double heart canoe,
very popular among honeymooners.

00:07:30.860 --> 00:07:35.440
This was a phrase I usually closed
the deal with, chopping out my y's

00:07:35.440 --> 00:07:39.940
and pronouncing popular
like a variety of tree.

00:07:39.940 --> 00:07:42.210
You can spot honeymooner
hands immediately.

00:07:42.210 --> 00:07:45.210
New bride usually fans her
fingers like piano players,

00:07:45.210 --> 00:07:47.670
hoping you'll ask about
her engagement ring

00:07:47.670 --> 00:07:50.780
so she can tell you all
the carats and setting.

00:07:50.780 --> 00:07:54.260
New groom is usually spinning
his new ring with his thumb,

00:07:54.260 --> 00:07:57.780
the way you might absently
work a burst blister.

00:07:57.780 --> 00:08:00.740
They wanted something
we could provide.

00:08:00.740 --> 00:08:03.800
Maintaining our tables we kept
the porter agreement alive.

00:08:03.800 --> 00:08:06.770
You can bet official parks
vendors had tried for years

00:08:06.770 --> 00:08:09.040
to justify breaking that treaty.

00:08:09.040 --> 00:08:12.850
What I had said, though, a
sales pitch was still true,

00:08:12.850 --> 00:08:15.730
the double heart canoe
was our signature item.

00:08:15.730 --> 00:08:19.340
You do best with something that's
like traditional Indian beadwork,

00:08:19.340 --> 00:08:22.710
but that also commemorates
something for the tourists.

00:08:22.710 --> 00:08:24.010
I helped design this.

00:08:24.010 --> 00:08:28.660
My family developed the beadwork
equivalent of the concert T-shirt,

00:08:28.660 --> 00:08:31.030
with tour dates and
cities on the back.

00:08:31.030 --> 00:08:34.730
You see, Niagara Falls is official
honeymoon capitol of the world.

00:08:34.730 --> 00:08:38.160
I'm not sure why a giant waterfall
above a bunch of sharp rocks made

00:08:38.160 --> 00:08:43.420
that cut, maybe because when people
get married they say they're taking

00:08:43.420 --> 00:08:45.800
the plunge.

00:08:45.800 --> 00:08:48.290
Together we came up
with this killer idea

00:08:48.290 --> 00:08:51.160
for the schatzki inclined
newlywed tourists.

00:08:51.160 --> 00:08:53.080 position:56%
My dad made little birch bark canoes

00:08:53.080 --> 00:08:57.720
that my mom stuffed two plump
velvet heart pincushions inside of.

00:08:57.720 --> 00:09:02.400 position:56%
We beaded the hearts with a date and
initials while the customer watched.

00:09:02.400 --> 00:09:05.480
I've carved so many initials and
hash marks into little hearts

00:09:05.480 --> 00:09:10.600
that I could maybe qualify as a
graffiti minded cardiac surgeon.

00:09:10.600 --> 00:09:14.340
Despite our signature,
our mom left our dad,

00:09:14.340 --> 00:09:16.570
his rental shack when I was eight.

00:09:16.570 --> 00:09:19.130
Our apartment was in
something called the projects,

00:09:19.130 --> 00:09:22.540
which made it seem like we lived
in a classroom science experiment.

00:09:22.540 --> 00:09:24.320
Add an Indian woman
and her kids to a set

00:09:24.320 --> 00:09:27.480
of low rent apartment buildings
jammed with too many people,

00:09:27.480 --> 00:09:30.460
all colors except white,
what happens?

00:09:30.460 --> 00:09:32.750
Do they bind and make
a new substance?

00:09:32.750 --> 00:09:36.950
If so, is it like epoxy or acid?

00:09:36.950 --> 00:09:39.610
Even after we moved out my
parents shared the treaty

00:09:39.610 --> 00:09:43.150
and short vendor permit, and
my mom still sold my dad's work

00:09:43.150 --> 00:09:45.970
since you needed a res address
to apply for the permit.

00:09:45.970 --> 00:09:50.110 position:56%
At first they refused to collaborate
on the double heart canoes.

00:09:50.110 --> 00:09:53.130
They each insisted they were
stuck with the hard part and,

00:09:53.130 --> 00:09:55.290
thus, should get a bigger cut.

00:09:55.290 --> 00:09:58.300
None of us kids dared suggest
we had the hardest part.

00:09:58.300 --> 00:10:00.080
Though it was true,
we had to chit-chat

00:10:00.080 --> 00:10:03.990 position:56%
with the newly in-love couples while
we maimed velvet hearts for them.

00:10:03.990 --> 00:10:06.570
The city wasn't a bad
place to finish out school,

00:10:06.570 --> 00:10:10.410 position:56%
and we did the same vendor table
gig we'd always done in the summers.

00:10:10.410 --> 00:10:12.730
It was like being near
a satellite reservation,

00:10:12.730 --> 00:10:14.540
at least in the summertime.

00:10:14.540 --> 00:10:17.580
The reservation heavy tavern
softball league teams played

00:10:17.580 --> 00:10:20.190
in the park near the projects.

00:10:20.190 --> 00:10:23.050
There were worse ways to spend your
summer evenings than watching men

00:10:23.050 --> 00:10:25.380
in tight uniforms running
around, every now

00:10:25.380 --> 00:10:30.710
and then rearranging their favorite
equipment inside those tight pants.

00:10:30.710 --> 00:10:34.420
Oh, hon, the new bride
said, isn't this the cutest?

00:10:34.420 --> 00:10:37.850
While new groom glanced at
the canoe, suddenly searching

00:10:37.850 --> 00:10:41.430
for a hangtag to see what
it was going to cost.

00:10:41.430 --> 00:10:43.880
We could smudge it with
some tobacco, Marie said,

00:10:43.880 --> 00:10:45.610
reaching under the
table for her purse

00:10:45.610 --> 00:10:48.510
where I knew she had
a pack of Kool's.

00:10:48.510 --> 00:10:52.470
Get you off on the right foot
for a lifetime of happiness.

00:10:52.470 --> 00:10:55.240
Is that extra, new groom asked?

00:10:55.240 --> 00:10:58.000
He had not yet learned his lines.

00:10:58.000 --> 00:11:01.850
My daughter jokes, our mom said,
kicking Marie under the table,

00:11:01.850 --> 00:11:06.550
just like on a sitcom except there
was no joke there, no stunt kicks.

00:11:06.550 --> 00:11:10.060
We do, though, offer to bead
your initials and the date,

00:11:10.060 --> 00:11:13.980
usually $10 extra, but this
beautiful Memorial Day,

00:11:13.980 --> 00:11:18.220
she said opening her arms wide
to provide her generosity,

00:11:18.220 --> 00:11:21.080
we give you that part for free.

00:11:21.080 --> 00:11:22.920
Oh, hon, new bride said.

00:11:22.920 --> 00:11:25.720
And new groom got out his wallet.

00:11:25.720 --> 00:11:28.630
My blushing bride here, he
said, grabbing her shoulders

00:11:28.630 --> 00:11:32.770 position:56%
and squeezing her close to him,
she's a DAR, so her mother wanted us

00:11:32.770 --> 00:11:36.260
to get married on the 4th of July.

00:11:36.260 --> 00:11:39.850
DAR, our mom said, burning
through her gas tank of charm,

00:11:39.850 --> 00:11:44.110
your name is Darlene, Darla?

00:11:44.110 --> 00:11:46.680
D-A-R, new bride said giggling,

00:11:46.680 --> 00:11:49.400
Daughters of the American
Revolution.

00:11:49.400 --> 00:11:51.680
It was important to my
mother, she hastened to add,

00:11:51.680 --> 00:11:54.210
my parents wanted us to get
married on the 4th of July,

00:11:54.210 --> 00:11:57.110
invite all their other DAR friends.

00:11:57.110 --> 00:11:58.840
We're from Concord.

00:11:58.840 --> 00:12:01.800
Apparently that was supposed
to mean something to us.

00:12:01.800 --> 00:12:03.800
But we're not really like that.

00:12:03.800 --> 00:12:08.100 position:56%
Then she leaned in conspiratorially,
we eloped to avoid a big production.

00:12:08.100 --> 00:12:10.560
So nice to have a memento.

00:12:10.560 --> 00:12:14.170 position:56%
If they want to throw us a reception
on Independence Day, great,

00:12:14.170 --> 00:12:18.330
but we get to be married
where and when we want.

00:12:18.330 --> 00:12:20.050
We've got beaded picture
frames, too,

00:12:20.050 --> 00:12:23.670
I said to new groom,
upping the ante.

00:12:23.670 --> 00:12:26.800
Make great thank you gifts
for your new in-laws.

00:12:26.800 --> 00:12:30.320
Got some here with two
beaded birds, like lovebirds.

00:12:30.320 --> 00:12:34.290
I hated using poor grammar, but it
tended to make the sale smoother.

00:12:34.290 --> 00:12:37.970
I revealed an elaborate
velvet beadwork picture frame.

00:12:37.970 --> 00:12:42.650
The bride ran her fingers over the
rich velvet, leaving little trails.

00:12:42.650 --> 00:12:45.360
I could even bead a couple
little bees on it, I said,

00:12:45.360 --> 00:12:50.290
joining her giggle, since this is
your honeymoon, birds and bees.

00:12:50.290 --> 00:12:51.800
New groom grinned.

00:12:51.800 --> 00:12:54.650
Not sure your mother would
care for that, he laughed.

00:12:54.650 --> 00:12:59.310
My mom was about to blow a gasket
thinking I'd lost the sale.

00:12:59.310 --> 00:13:02.480
Might be kind of a fun
secret joke, he added,

00:13:02.480 --> 00:13:04.810
how long before it could be ready?

00:13:04.810 --> 00:13:08.860
Fifteen minutes, I said, I could
do this beading in my sleep.

00:13:08.860 --> 00:13:12.370
Half hour, our mom interrupted,
handing the double heart canoe

00:13:12.370 --> 00:13:15.090
to Marie and digging
out her receipt book.

00:13:15.090 --> 00:13:18.120
My daughters work quick, but
it's very trick work, she said,

00:13:18.120 --> 00:13:20.940
doing a double drop y, as I had.

00:13:20.940 --> 00:13:23.200
I made big eyes at Marie.

00:13:23.200 --> 00:13:27.030
My mom asked for 50% down since
we couldn't sell it to anyone else

00:13:27.030 --> 00:13:28.790
with their initials on it.

00:13:28.790 --> 00:13:32.650 position:56%
The groom, still chuckling about
the secret sexy joke he'd be playing

00:13:32.650 --> 00:13:36.220
on his mother-in-law,
said he'd pay in full.

00:13:36.220 --> 00:13:37.670
When our mom got their initials

00:13:37.670 --> 00:13:40.780
for the custom beading
she showed him the receipt

00:13:40.780 --> 00:13:42.940
with $100 in the total line.

00:13:42.940 --> 00:13:46.960
His eyes bugged, but I was
already breaking out my yellow

00:13:46.960 --> 00:13:50.130
and black beads to do
a couple quick bumbles.

00:13:50.130 --> 00:13:54.360
He paid and they watched their art
